<TITLE> BNP walks out a second time </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 2 (bdnews24.com)  BNP walked a second time on Wednesday protesting the closure of a BNP-leaning Bengali daily, Amar Desh, and arrest of its acting editor Mahmudur Rahman. This time the main opposition stayed for just about half an hour since their return at 7:35pm. The opposition had walked out in protest on Wednesday even before the budget session got down to business inside five minutes of the day's session. BNP's Moudud Ahmed had stood up for a point of order as speaker Abdul Hamid was giving floor to prime minister Sheikh Hasina for taking questions for the first 30 minutes of the opening day. Hamid promised the BNP leader floor provided the opposition MPs to listen to the prime minister first, saying :"This is not the right time." "There is no scope in the Rules of Procedure to give point of order during the question-answer hour," Hamid explained. After the speaker's ruling, Moudud silently led the BNP MPs out, mainly to avoid the prime minister's question-answer hour, the BNP insiders say. "You are not abiding by the Rules of Procedure. This is really unfortunate," said Hamid. Earlier, Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury MP, who sits on the policymaking standing committee, told bdnews24.com they will join the key proceedings. bd
